      ],
      "message": "Rework CChain::Next() to take ref, return optional ref\n\nTo minimize chance of erroneous nullptr dereference, `CChain::Next()`\nis changed to take a reference instead of a pointer. The return pointer\nis changed to optional reference. The case when there is no next\n(tip or not found) is thus represented by `nullopt`.\nA type alias is introduced for the lengthy optional-reference type.\nCall sites have been adapted, in some places iterating using a pointer,\nin some using a optional reference for the iterator (as it was more fit).",
