      "body": "I don't understand this change. An optional reference is a pointer. Using something other than a pointer is just extra steps.\n\n\nIf you want to change the code, my recommendation would be to look at *high level* functions that take a block as argument, and then see if it makes sense to pass that block index as a reference.\n\nSee also https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34416#discussion_r2730835553",
